HEADWORD: Hoppestere
<hw>Hop`pes*tere"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>An unexplained
epithet used by Chaucer in reference to ships. By some it is defined as
⟦ldquo⟧dancing (on the wave)⟦rdquo⟧; by others as
⟦ldquo⟧opposing,⟦rdquo⟧ ⟦ldquo⟧warlike.⟦rdquo⟧</def> <rj><au>T. R.
Lounsbury.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hoppet</ent>⟦br⟧
